ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-ship-performer-careers-jobs-travel-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebe%20a%20singer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20generously%20supported%20my%20newfound%20dreams%2C%20my%20mother%20trucking%20me%20to%20rehearsals%2C%20recitals%2C%20and%20lessons%20where%20I%20trained%20in%20opera%20and%20musical%20theater.%20Throughout%20middle%20and%20high%20school%2C%20I%20had%20opportunities%20to%20sing%20choir%20solos%2C%20performed%20lead%20roles%20in%20musicals%2C%20and%20sang%20in%20a%20barbershop%20quartet%20for%20three%20years%20(by%20far%20the%20most%20fun%20experience).%20It%20was%20fun%E2%80%A6at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20spotlight%2C%20but%20this%20fulfillment%20gradually%20evolved%20into%20anxiety%20and%20self-doubt%2C%20fueling%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Focd-symptoms-more-intense-worse-people-love-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealready%20debilitating%20OCD%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20depression%20I'd%20struggled%20with%20since%20early%20childhood.%20The%20downside%20of%20basing%20your%20goals%20on%20applause%20is%20that%20your%20future%20becomes%20inextricably%20linked%20to%20other%20people's%20reactions.%20Every%20performance%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20followed%20by%20bottomless%20feelings%20of%20inadequacy.%20Around%20this%20time%2C%20I%20also%20started%20to%20experiment%20with%20drinking%20and%20smoking%2C%20which%20eased%20the%20tensions%20that%20flooded%20my%20mind%2C%20though%20I%20only%20did%20both%20occasionally%20for%20fear%20of%20negatively%20impacting%20my%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bfec3bb-ba23-4914-8faf-c3e4cfe18142%5C%22%3EA%20tonsillectomy%20changed%20my%20voice%2C%20and%20I%20quit%20singing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grades%20were%20lacking%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20factors%20both%20in%20and%20out%20of%20my%20control%3A%20mental%20illness%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-called-over-40-pharmacies-to-get-my-adderall-prescription-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eundiagnosed%20ADHD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bullying%2C%20and%20poor%20personal%20choices.%20When%20college%20application%20season%20rolled%20around%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20music%20was%20my%20only%20chance%20for%20acceptance%20anywhere.%20In%20the%20fall%2C%20I%20started%20at%20a%20music%20conservatory%20in%20southern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20freshman%20year%2C%20I%20underwent%20a%20tonsillectomy%20after%20years%20of%20chronic%20illness%20that%20left%20my%20neck%20swollen%20with%20discomfort.%20Initially%2C%20I%20was%20heartbroken%20by%20the%20surgery's%20effects%20%E2%80%94%20my%20range%20was%20dramatically%20reduced%2C%20and%20I%20sounded%20like%20a%20different%20person.%20Even%20my%20sneezes%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20anguish%20turned%20into%20relief%2C%20however%2C%20when%20I%20reflected%20on%20my%20progress%20in%20the%20music%20program%20and%20got%20honest%20with%20myself.%20To%20be%20frank%2C%20I%20hated%20performing.%20I%20no%20longer%20took%20pride%20or%20comfort%20in%20singing%20and%20was%20acutely%20aware%20that%20I%20was%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20go%20pro.%20When%20I%20confided%20this%20realization%20to%20friends%2C%20many%20assumed%20I%20was%20being%20performatively%20modest%20or%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-executive-combats-manages-imposter-syndrome-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimposter%20syndrome%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20I%20was%20simply%20being%20realistic.%20So%20I%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20change%20steered%20me%20toward%20writing%2C%20my%20eventual%20career%20path%2C%20but%20it%20also%20meant%20I%20suddenly%20had%20permission%20to%20smoke%20and%20drink%20as%20much%20as%20I%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20spare%20you%20the%20specifics%20of%20my%20drinking%20career.%20The%20details%20are%20both%20gory%20and%20generic.%20Suffice%20it%20to%20say%20that%20I%20am%20a%20%26quot%3Bgarden-variety%20drunk%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20we%20say%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fovercoming-alcohol-use-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12-step%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20helped%20me%20get%20sober.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%3A%20I%20haven't%20had%20a%20drink%20in%202.5%20years.%20The%20bad%20news%20is%20that%20I%20subsequently%20leaned%20into%20every%20other%20crutch%20on%20the%20menu%3A%20vaping%2C%20over-caffeination%2C%20disordered%20eating%2C%20binge-watching%2C%20isolating%2C%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20smoking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e16288d-3fdf-44d5-9bc5-a291b1eb385a%5C%22%3EPutting%20down%20the%20cigarettes%20helped%20bring%20my%20voice%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20common%20adage%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20quit%20our%20vices%20in%20the%20order%20that%20they're%20killing%20us.%26quot%3B%20Early%20on%20in%20my%20sobriety%2C%20I%20confessed%20my%20reliance%20on%20Red%20Bull%20and%20cigarettes%20to%20my%20therapist%2C%20sheepishly%20acknowledging%20that%20I%20should%20stop.%20Her%20response%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-quit-smoking-for-the-new-year-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equit%20smoking%3C%2Fa%3E%20right%20now.%20Do%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20stop%20drinking%20caffeine.%26quot%3B%20I%20followed%20her%20instructions%2C%20and%20after%20the%20initial%20rough%20period%20of%20about%20a%20year%2C%20I%20felt%20ready%20to%20break%20up%20with%20smoking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuitting%20took%20another%20nine%20months%2C%20and%20while%20I'm%20not%20free%20of%20nicotine%20dependency%2C%20saying%20goodbye%20to%20cigarettes%20has%20been%20miraculous.%20Aside%20from%20the%20cost%2C%20smell%2C%20and%20obvious%20health%20consequences%2C%20smoking%20eroded%20my%20voice%20for%20years%2C%20preventing%20it%20from%20recovering%20to%20its%20pre-surgical%20state%2C%20and%20while%20I%20figured%20that%20my%20complexion%2C%20hair%2C%20and%20nails%20would%20likely%20improve%2C%20I%20didn't%20expect%20the%20biggest%20shift%3A%20my%20voice%20came%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20by%20little%2C%20I%20started%20picking%20up%20music%20again%20as%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessional-opera-singer-lost-his-voice-because-of-cord-paralysis-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evocal%20cords%3C%2Fa%3E%20slowly%20but%20surely%20regained%20their%20flexibility.%20At%2035%2C%20no%20aspect%20of%20my%20livelihood%20involves%20music%2C%20so%20it%20feels%20like%20I%20can%20actually%20take%20joy%20in%20it%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20anyone%20else%20hears%20and%20approves.%20Now%2C%20sitting%20down%20for%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20in%20front%20of%20the%20piano%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20a%20chore%20so%20much%20as%20a%20reward%20for%20finally%20taking%20care%20of%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-smoking-cigarettes-love-singing-music-again-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741685821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cf1decb8b41a9673fa2c97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-smoking-cigarettes-love-singing-music-again-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20singer%2C%20but%20when%20I%20let%20go%20of%20that%20dream%2C%20I%20picked%20up%20cigarettes.%20Quitting%20smoking%20helped%20me%20to%20love%20music%20again.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sam%20Escobar)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-smoking-cigarettes-love-singing-music-again-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20is%20Amazon%20founder%20Jeff%20Bezo