s%20almost%20comical.%20Just%20when%20you%20think%20there%20could%20not%20be%20any%20more%2C%20more%20step%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20men%20ended%20up%20forming%20an%20%26quot%3Bimpenetrable%20dividing%20line%26quot%3B%20between%20Xi's%20and%20Zuckerberg's%20dressing%20rooms%2C%20Wynn-Williams%20wrote%2C%20calling%20them%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20Chinese%20wall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Xi%20is%20so%20obscured%20that%20he%20doesn't%20even%20have%20to%20risk%20making%20eye%20contact%20with%20Mark%2C%26quot%3B%20Wynn-Williams%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20Xi's%20men%20dispersed%20after%20he%20entered%20his%20dressing%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUh%2C%20I%20guess%20that%20pull-aside%20isn't%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20told%20his%20staff%2C%20per%20Wynn-Williams'%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20Zuckerberg%20has%20managed%20to%20meet%20Xi%20on%20other%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202015%2C%20Zuckerberg%20got%20to%20speak%20to%20Xi%20when%20the%20Chinese%20leader%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-leaders-greet-chinese-president-2015-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisited%20Seattle%20for%20a%20two-day%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20conversed%20briefly%2C%20and%20Zuckerberg%20later%20posted%20an%20image%20of%20himself%20with%20Xi%20on%20Facebook.%20Zuckerberg%20said%20he%20spoke%20to%20Xi%20entirely%20in%20Chinese%2C%20and%20called%20the%20moment%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Emeaningful%20personal%20milestone%3C%2Fspan%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20October%202017%2C%20Zuckerberg%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple's%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETim%20Cook%3C%2Fa%3E%20met%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-and-mark-zuckerberg-meet-with-china-president-xi-jinping-in-beijing-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXi%20at%20Tsinghua%20University's%20business%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWynn-Williams%20%E2%80%94%20an%20international%20lawyer%20and%20former%20New%20Zealand%20diplomat%20%E2%80%94%20joined%20Facebook%20in%202011%20and%20became%20its%20director%20of%20global%20public%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20book%2C%20Wynn-Williams%20gave%20her%20account%20of%20Facebook's%20efforts%20to%20enter%20the%20Chinese%20market.%20Facebook's%20leaders%20considered%20making%20major%20concessions%2C%20including%20letting%20Beijing%20control%20how%20and%20what%20content%20was%20displayed%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20book%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20stories%20in%20it%20came%20from%20%26quot%3Ban%20employee%20terminated%20eight%20years%20ago%20for%20poor%20performance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20operate%20our%20services%20in%20China%20today.%20It%20is%20no%20secret%20we%20were%20once%20interested%20in%20doing%20so%20as%20part%20of%20Facebook's%20effort%20to%20connect%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20widely%20reported%20beginning%20a%20decade%20ago.%20We%20ultimately%20opted%20not%20to%20go%20through%20with%20the%20ideas%20we'd%20explored%2C%20which%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20announced%20in%202019%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20response%20to%20Wynn-Williams'%20book%2C%20Facebook%20also%20directed%20BI%20to%20Zuckerberg's%20comments%20on%20China%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Zuckerberg's%202019%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F10%2Fmark-zuckerberg-stands-for-voice-and-free-expression%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Georgetown%20University%20%E2%80%94%20he%20objected%20to%20the%20censorship%20of%20protests%20on%20platforms%20like%20Facebook's%20competitor%2C%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20then%20called%20censorship%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20reasons%20we%20don't%20operate%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20or%20our%20other%20services%20in%20China.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20our%20services%20in%20China%20because%20I%20believe%20in%20connecting%20the%20whole%20world%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20we%20might%20help%20create%20a%20more%20open%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20worked%20hard%20to%20make%20this%20happen.%20But%20we%20could%20never%20come%20to%20agreement%20on%20what%20it%20would%20take%20for%20us%20to%20operate%20there%2C%20and%20they%20never%20let%20us%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook%20never%20made%20it%20across%20China's%20Great%20Firewall%20%E2%80%94%20and%20as%20of%20today%2C%20Meta's%20core%20products%20remain%20shut%20out%20of%20China's%20insular%20social%20media%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20operate%20an%20ecosystem%20of%20social%20media%20applications%20that%20function%20independently%20of%20their%20Western%20versions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fchina-tech-baidu-shares-soar-ernie-ai-bot-free-deepseek-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBaidu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-superapp-wechat-best-feature-walkthrough-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeChat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshanghai-lockdown-china-twitter-weibo-censor-content-food-shortage-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeibo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frednote-fast-becoming-regular-american-window-into-china-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXiaohongshu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20